title: Russia hawks exploit blogger's death to demand executions and an even harsher crackdown on dissent
description: The killing of Russian military journalist Vladlen Tatarsky has set off angry demands among politicians and commentators in Russia for the return of the death penalty, and for a merciless crackdown on dissent through greater use of terrorism and treason charges.

title: Four children killed in axe attack at daycare center in southern Brazil
description: Four children have been killed and four more injured in an axe attack at a daycare center in the southern Brazilian city of Blumenau.

title: Husband of former Scottish First Minister arrested over party finances investigation
description: The husband of former Scottish First Minister Nicola Sturgeon, Peter Murrell, was arrested on Wednesday in connection with an investigation into the funding and finances of the Scottish National Party.

title: Tunisian president's mystery 'disappearance' raises questions about his health
description: Tunisian President Kais Saied's almost two-week absence has raised questions about his health and succession in a country that has become increasingly authoritarian since he took power.

title: Clashes erupt inside the al-Aqsa mosque after Israeli forces enter
description: Israeli police clashed with Palestinians inside the al-Aqsa mosque in Jerusalem's Old City early on Wednesday, just days after a Palestinian man was killed outside the holy site.

title: Opinion: Why did we ever think scooters were a good idea?
description: The people of Paris have spoken loud and clear: get electric scooters off of our streets.

title: Man sentenced for abducting girl from family's tent at remote Australian campsite
description: A man who admitted abducting a four-year-old girl from a remote campsite in Western Australia and holding her for 18 days during a massive police search has been sentenced to 13 years and 6 months in prison.

title: European leaders head to Beijing with hope of driving peace in Ukraine, while balancing business ties
description: French President Emmanuel Macron and European Commission chief Ursula von der Leyen arrive in Beijing Wednesday for a visit France has framed as a high stakes chance to push China to do more for peace in Ukraine, but where European economic interests will also loom large.
